article.headline: Eastern Kentucky 31, Samford 12
article.story: BIRMINGHAM, Ala. (AP) -- Josh Greco completed 18-of-28 passes for 323 yards and two long touchdowns as Eastern Kentucky came from behind to defeat Samford 31-12 Saturday. Eastern Kentucky (2-4, 1-2 Ohio Valley Conference) fell behind 6-0 in the first quarter, but stormed back with two touchdowns in the second quarter and cruised to an easy win. The Colonels had 481 total yards to 289 for Samford (2-4, 0-3). Mark Dunn rushed 19 times for 109 yards for the Colonels and scored on two one-yard runs. Greco completed a 36-yard touchdown pass to Bobby Washington in the second quarter and hit Quinton Williams with a 73-yard scoring toss early in the fourth quarter. The Colonels also got a 27-yard field goal from Taylor Long. Samford took the early lead on first quarter field goals of 35 and 39 yards by Shannon Fleming. The Bulldogs tacked on another score with less than four minutes to play on a 23-yard pass from Alex Mortensen to Jeff Moore.
